{{Infobox television | show_name = STEM in 30 | image = | caption = | genre = Education | starring = Beth Wilson Marty Kelsey | country = [[United States]] | language = English | num_seasons = 5 | num_episodes = 46 | executive_producer = Mark Kornmann (2014-2018) | producer = Jon Boyette Paul Griffith | editor = Ryan Shank (2018-) | camera = multi-camera | runtime = 30 min. | distributor = National Air and Space Museum | channel = NASA-TV | first_aired = 2014 | website = https://airandspace.si.edu/connect/stem-30 }}
'''STEM in 30''' is an online [[Online learning community|educational program]] produced by the [[National Air and Space Museum]] in [[Washington, D.C.]] hosted by Marty Kelsey and Beth Wilson.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://airandspace.si.edu/connect/stem-30|title=STEM in 30|date=2016-06-13|work=National Air and Space Museum|access-date=2018-07-09|language=en}}</ref> Each episode is typically 30 minutes and features special guests and different [[science]], [[Mathematics|math]], [[engineering]] or technology topics.<ref>{{Cite journal|date=2015-04-03|title=Smithsonian's National Air and Space Museum Launches Stem Webcast Series|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-408131388.html}}</ref> Since first broadcasting in 2014, the program has covered dozens of topics including the [[NASA]]'s [[Apollo program]], [[Tuskegee Airmen]], astronaut training, the [[Wright brothers]] and the [[Orion (spacecraft)|Orion]] program.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://airandspace.si.edu/connect/stem-30/archive|title=Archive|date=2016-06-14|work=National Air and Space Museum|access-date=2018-07-09|language=en}}</ref> The first four seasons of the show were [[Live broadcast|broadcast live]] with a student audience. With it's fifth season, STEM in 30 has switched its format to a pre-taped show with a live question and answer session about that months topic with an expert a week later.
