{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
'''''Uriaș''''' (plural ''uriași'') is the common [[Romanian language|Romanian-language]] designation of [[Giant (mythology)|giants]], who are prominent figures in [[Romanian folklore]]. There are several varieties of ''uriași'', who share most of their traits but have different names from one [[Historical regions of Romania|historical region]] of [[Romania]] to another. Thus, '''''Jidovi''''' is the term used mainly in [[Oltenia]], and its bearers are supposed to be creators of large mounds, and, in some legends, they play an evil role. '''''Novaci''''' is used mainly in [[Muntenia]], for creatures who are mainly associated with the [[Southern Carpathians]].

